sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM purchases
WHERE purchase_date >= date('now', '-1 month');

external_knowledge:
- 'travelers' refers to customers;
- 'voyages' metaphorically refers to purchase activities;
- 'vast ocean of purchases' refers to the aggregate purchase activity;
- 'remain silent' or 'slammed the door' refers to no response or a 'declined' response to the campaign;
- 'marketing whisper' refers to the marketing campaign.

- Young upstarts: Customers born after 1980 with an annual income over $60,000;
- Luxury goods: Products with a price greater than $100;
- Ventured into acquiring: Made at least one purchase;
- Done so more than once: Bought the same or different luxury goods more than one time.

sql:
SELECT SUM(CAST(REPLACE(p.amount, ',', '') AS REAL)) AS total_amount
FROM purchases p
JOIN complaints c ON p.customer_id = c.customer_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS customer_count
FROM purchases
WHERE purchase_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
